        <h2>Professional story</h2>
        <p>For most of my career I have worked in platform and infrastructure engineering — building streaming platforms, migration and infrastructure automation, observability, and the reliability tooling that large engineering organizations depend on. The common thread is turning repeated infrastructure pain into reusable platform capabilities that other teams can rely on.</p>
        <p>At JP Morgan Chase I spent several years deep in distributed streaming systems and platform automation. At Microsoft I work on secured, ephemeral sandbox platforms for security researchers and secured multicloud Kubernetes infrastructure, with a strong focus on security posture, isolation, and automation.</p>
        <p>Outside of work, I build tools from scratch and learn in public — sharing write-ups and open-source projects so others can learn from them too. I am looking for senior, lead, or staff platform/infrastructure engineering roles where I can build reliable distributed systems, cloud platforms, and developer-facing infrastructure at scale.</p>
